    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This collector-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) showcases the pinnacle of naturally aspirated engineering. Power is delivered by the S54B32 inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and a 7,900 RPM redline. This unit has undergone a comprehensive preventative maintenance suite, including a Beisan Systems VANOS overhaul and WPC-treated rod bearing replacement. The chassis is structurally optimized with a TMS subframe reinforcement kit and rides on Bilstein PSS10 adjustable coilovers for precise damping control. Power reaches the rear wheels through a crisp 6-speed manual gearbox and a factory limited-slip differential. The exterior retains its factory luster with zero signs of oxidation or panel misalignment, while the undercarriage remains dry and free of corrosion. This is a turn-key, mechanically flawless example of the ultimate driving machine.",
